\nThe broader structure story begins in late June, when AUD/USD was grinding along the 0.6886\u20130.6894 area, unable to find meaningful direction. The catalyst for change arrived in the 14\u201315 July window, where a forceful two-day surge carried price from the 0.6913 region all the way to a session high of 0.7021, a move of roughly 110 pips that broke the pair cleanly above the prior congestion. That advance stalled into the 0.7021\u20130.7027 area, which has since acted as a ceiling across multiple daily closes. The pair has been unable to reclaim or sustain trade above the structure resistance zone marked at 0.6989, which has now capped at least two meaningful intraday rallies. Below current price, the prior reaction zone around 0.6960 has attracted buyers on each test \u2014 four touches in the data \u2014 making it the key near-term structural floor. A more significant support cluster sits considerably lower near 0.6864, representing the base from which the July rally originated.\n\nOn the H1 timeframe, the picture is one of orderly drift lower from the 0.7021 peak reached during the 23 July Asian session. Price sold off in a fairly steady sequence through the European and US hours of Wednesday, finding a floor around 0.6962\u20130.6965 in the early hours of Thursday before stabilising. Since then, the hourly candles have been constructive but modest \u2014 a gentle recovery back toward the 0.6975\u20130.6980 area \u2014 with no real momentum behind the bid. The market looks to be in a wait-and-see posture, consolidating within roughly 15 pips either side of current levels.\n\nThe calendar is empty for today, which removes the prospect of a scheduled volatility event forcing a directional break. In the absence of a catalyst, the pair is likely to remain anchored within the 0.6960\u20130.6989 range, with price action driven primarily by broader USD sentiment and any risk-appetite shifts in equities or commodities.\n\nWhat would change the read? A daily close above the structure resistance at 0.6989 would reopen the case for a retest of the 0.7021 highs and potentially the longer-term prior reaction zone at 0.7184. Conversely, a clean break and close beneath the 0.6960 prior reaction zone would shift the near-term bias toward the downside, with the 0.6864 support region becoming the next area of structural interest. Until one of those scenarios materialises, the neutral framing holds.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}